verbose_text: The mechanism of intracrinology explains the local effect of DHEA as well as the results of several studies that have demonstrated an absence of increased blood oestrogen and testosterone levels after DHEA administration for up to 12 months [XREF_BIBR - XREF_BIBR], which in turn means that side effects are almost absent : Labrie et al. reported vaginal discharge due to melting of the vehicle at body temperature in 6% of women during intravaginal DHEA administration [XREF_BIBR].
